<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About Zoro | Company and Operating Principles</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
    <header class="site-header">
        <div class="container nav-shell">
            <a href="index.html" class="brand-mark">Zoro</a>
            <nav class="site-nav" aria-label="Primary navigation">
                <a href="index.html" class="nav-link">Home</a>
                <a href="platform.html" class="nav-link">Platform</a>
                <a href="pricing.html" class="nav-link">Pricing</a>
                <a href="company.html" class="nav-link active">Company</a>
                <a href="contact.html" class="nav-link">Contact</a>
            </nav>
            <div class="nav-actions">
                <button class="theme-toggle" type="button" aria-label="Toggle dark theme" data-theme-toggle>
                    <span class="theme-toggle-light">Light</span>
                    <span class="theme-toggle-dark">Dark</span>
                </button>
                <a href="contact.html" class="btn btn-primary">Book a Demo</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section class="page-hero">
            <div class="container narrow">
                <span class="eyebrow">Company</span>
                <h1>Zoro exists to make software delivery easier to trust.</h1>
                <p>
                    Instead of another generic about page, this one explains the company’s point of view and gives the site
                    a credible story behind the product.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section surface-muted">
            <div class="container split-section">
                <div>
                    <span class="eyebrow">What we believe</span>
                    <h2>Engineering teams move faster when operational systems are legible.</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="stack-list">
                    <article class="stack-item">
                        <h3>Releases should be understandable</h3>
                        <p>People should know what changed, where it went, and what to do if something breaks.</p>
                    </article>
                    <article class="stack-item">
                        <h3>Self-service needs guardrails</h3>
                        <p>Teams need autonomy, but production systems still need ownership, approvals, and traceability.</p>
                    </article>
                    <article class="stack-item">
                        <h3>Operations is part of product quality</h3>
                        <p>Runtime health, release velocity, and recovery speed shape the user experience as much as code quality.</p>
                    </article>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="principles" class="section">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="card-grid three-up">
                    <article class="info-card">
                        <h3>Plain workflows</h3>
                        <p>Zoro favors clear release stages and ownership over hidden automation and opaque orchestration.</p>
                    </article>
                    <article class="info-card">
                        <h3>Production accountability</h3>
                        <p>Every service should have visible ownership, active health signals, and 
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

 
</body>
</html>
